08/03/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The ruling New Democracy (ND) party views its first year in power as successful, Minister of State Thodoris Roussopoulos said at a news conference Monday (7 March), citing the successful conduct of the 2004 Olympics, legislative improvements and intensified efforts against corruption and bribery as the key achievements of the government led by Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis. 
A year ago, ND defeated its main rival PASOK in parliamentary elections, returning to power for the first time in 11 years. 
(ANA - 07/03/05)
